The paper deals with decoding linear block codes using neural belief propagation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves machine learning techniques to tailor the parity-check matrix, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for decoding, which could be classified under neural networks (cs.NE) or signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques to improve the performance of the decoder, which could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
